In the wake of his departure, a transitional government was put in place alongside with General National Congress. Then, during General National Congress six-year term another contralto transitional government stepped in and the country held general elections. Finally, the General National Congress allowed for a Constituent Assembly and then a new government was formed. In the meantime, significant and worrying events happened in Libya. To this end, the first significant event that happened included the killing of Jamal Dunia Ansar al-Sharia representative and then, the collapse of Sirte city. In March 2011 another important incident happened as more than 500 people were killed in a massacre in Trax Tumar city, south Libya. Security does seem to be a major preoccupation in Libya and many are the terrorist organizations that pose a severe danger for security and for Libyan culture and identity.
